1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:04,421
DOCTOR: Oh, it's a sanctuary base!
Deep space exploration.

2
00:00:04,546 --> 00:00:06,298
"Welcome to hell.”

3
00:00:06,423 --> 00:00:08,175
DOCTOR: What are you lot doing here?

4
00:00:08,258 --> 00:00:11,178
-That's a black hole.
-But that's impossible.

5
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:15,349
This lump of rock is suspended
in perpetual geostationary orbit

6
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:18,268
around that black hole, without falling in.

7
00:00:18,352 --> 00:00:21,063
There's some sort of power source
holding us here.

8
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:22,814
We're drilling down to try and find it.

9
00:00:25,609 --> 00:00:26,902
The Tardis is gone.

10
00:00:26,985 --> 00:00:29,863
Well, whatever it is down there,
it's not a natural phenomenon.

11
00:00:29,947 --> 00:00:32,741
And there was some form of civilisation.

12
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:34,159
They buried something.

13
00:00:37,329 --> 00:00:39,540
-What are they called?
-They're the Ood.

14
00:00:39,623 --> 00:00:40,832
Basic slave race.

15
00:00:40,916 --> 00:00:43,710
There's something happening with the Ood.

16
00:00:43,794 --> 00:00:46,255
THE OOD: And you will worship him.

17
00:00:46,338 --> 00:00:47,631
(GROWLING)

18
00:00:49,925 --> 00:00:53,845
You can tell Toby
we've found his civilisation.

19
00:00:54,096 --> 00:00:55,889
(DISTORTED VOICE)
These are the words of the Beast.

20
00:00:55,973 --> 00:00:57,641
And he has woken.

21
00:00:57,766 --> 00:01:01,186
I have been imprisoned for eternity.

22
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:03,063
But no more.

23
00:01:03,146 --> 00:01:05,148
BEAST: The Pit is open

24
00:01:06,191 --> 00:01:09,987
and I am free!

25
00:01:12,364 --> 00:01:14,700
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

26
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:51,695
Open fire!

27
00:01:59,077 --> 00:02:02,581
We're stabilising. We've got orbit.

28
00:02:07,711 --> 00:02:12,966
Doctor? Doctor, can you hear me?
Doctor, Ida, are you there?

29
00:02:14,718 --> 00:02:16,511
It's me!

30
00:02:17,387 --> 00:02:20,265
But they're coming. It's the Ood.

31
00:02:20,349 --> 00:02:21,975
-They've gone mad.
-How many of them?

32
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,769
All of them, all 50.

33
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:25,646
Danny, out of the way. Out of the way!

34
00:02:25,729 --> 00:02:28,732
But they're armed. It's the interface device.

35
00:02:28,815 --> 00:02:30,942
I don't know how,
but they're using it as a weapon.

36
00:02:38,992 --> 00:02:41,078
Close door 1.

37
00:02:50,337 --> 00:02:53,340
Open door 1. Close door 1.

38
00:02:53,423 --> 00:02:55,717
Lockdown! Seal door 1!

39
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:59,429
DANNY: Seal door 25.
Seal door 24. Seal door 23/

40
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:01,264
Jefferson, what's happening there?

41
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:04,601
I've got very little ammunition, sir.
How about you?

42
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:10,190
All I've got is a bolt-gun with, uh,
all of one bolt.

43
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:14,111
I could take out a grand total of one Ood.
Fat lot of good that is.

44
00:03:14,194 --> 00:03:17,072
Given the emergency,
I recommend strategy nine.

45
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:21,868
Strategy nine agreed.
Right, we need to get everyone together.

46
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:25,038
Rose, what about Ida and the Doctor?
Any word?

47
00:03:25,122 --> 00:03:29,209
I can't get a reply. Just nothing.
I keep trying, but it's...

48
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:32,295
DOCTOR: No, sorry. I'm fine. Still here!

49
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:34,131
You could have said, you stupid...

50
00:03:34,256 --> 00:03:35,507
(RADIO FEEDBACK)

51
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:37,050
Whoa, careful!

52
00:03:37,134 --> 00:03:39,886
Anyway, it's both of us, me and Ida. Hello!

53
00:03:39,970 --> 00:03:44,141
But the seal opened up. It's gone.

54
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:47,894
All we've got left is this chasm.

55
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:52,065
-ZACK: How deep is it?
-Can't tell. Looks like it goes down forever.

56
00:03:52,149 --> 00:03:55,235
The Pit is open. That's what the voice said.

57
00:03:55,318 --> 00:03:59,406
But there's nothing.
I mean, there's nothing coming out?

58
00:03:59,489 --> 00:04:02,159
No, no, no. No sign of the Beast.

59
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:03,618
It said Satan.

60
00:04:03,702 --> 00:04:05,495
Come on, Rose. Keep it together.

61
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:09,416
Is there no such thing? Doctor?

62
00:04:11,585 --> 00:04:13,503
Doctor, tell me there's no such thing.

63
00:04:13,587 --> 00:04:17,090
Ida, I recommend
that you withdraw immediately.

64
00:04:17,174 --> 00:04:19,593
But we've come all this way.

65
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:22,345
Okay, that was an order. Withdraw!

66
00:04:22,429 --> 00:04:24,681
When that thing opened,
the whole planet shifted.

67
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:26,600
One more inch
and we fall into the black hole

68
00:04:26,725 --> 00:04:28,602
so this thing stops right now.

69
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:31,438
But it's not much better up there
with the Ood.

70
00:04:31,563 --> 00:04:33,648
I'm initiating strategy nine

71
00:04:33,732 --> 00:04:37,486
so I need the two of you
back up top immediately. No...

72
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:41,490
Ida? Ida?

73
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:43,867
What do you think?

74
00:04:45,202 --> 00:04:46,620
He gave an order.

75
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:49,956
Yeah, but what do you think?

76
00:04:52,918 --> 00:04:56,129
It said, "I am the temptation.”

77
00:04:59,716 --> 00:05:04,971
If there's something in there,
why is it still hiding?

78
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:09,476
Maybe we opened the prison
but not the cell.

79
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,480
We should go down.

80
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:16,066
I'd go.

81
00:05:17,275 --> 00:05:18,985
What about you?

82
00:05:19,069 --> 00:05:21,738
Oh, in a second. But then again...

83
00:05:24,074 --> 00:05:26,076
That is so human.

84
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:29,079
Where angels fear to tread.

85
00:05:30,247 --> 00:05:32,999
Even now, standing on the edge,

86
00:05:34,376 --> 00:05:37,087
it's that feeling you get, yeah?

87
00:05:38,672 --> 00:05:40,715
Right at the back of your head.

88
00:05:41,383 --> 00:05:45,804
That impulse, that strange little impulse.

89
00:05:46,888 --> 00:05:51,476
That mad little voice saying,
"Go on, go on, go on.

90
00:05:51,768 --> 00:05:54,229
"Go over, go on."

91
00:05:56,064 --> 00:05:58,650
Maybe it's relying on that.

92
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:03,947
For once in my life, Officer Scott,

93
00:06:04,072 --> 00:06:06,199
I'm going to say...

94
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:11,037
retreat.

95
00:06:12,664 --> 00:06:16,293
Now I know I'm getting old.
Rose, we're coming back.

96
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:20,213
Best news I've heard all day.

97
00:06:20,297 --> 00:06:21,715
What are you doing?

98
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:25,468
He's infected. He brought
that thing on board. You saw it.

99
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:28,847
Are you gonna start shooting your own
people now? Is that what you're gonna do?

100
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:30,849
-Is it?
-If necessary.

101
00:06:30,932 --> 00:06:34,978
Well, then you'll have to shoot me,
if necessary. So what's it gonna be?

102
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:40,650
Look at his face. Whatever it was, it's gone.

103
00:06:40,734 --> 00:06:43,153
It passed into the Ood. You saw it happen.

104
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:45,822
He's clean.

105
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:51,328
Any sign of trouble, I shoot him.

106
00:06:52,954 --> 00:06:54,539
You all right?

107
00:06:56,124 --> 00:06:57,167
Yeah.

108
00:06:58,126 --> 00:07:00,253
-I don't know.
-Can you remember anything?

109
00:07:00,337 --> 00:07:03,006
Just... It was so angry.

110
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:07,677
It was fury and rage and death.

111
00:07:11,306 --> 00:07:12,974
It was him.

112
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:15,602
It was the Devil.

113
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:18,104
Come here.

114
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:26,446
DOCTOR: What's strategy nine?

115
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:31,493
IDA: Open the airlocks.
We'll be safe inside the lockdown.

116
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:33,828
The Ood will get thrown out
into the vacuum.

117
00:07:33,912 --> 00:07:36,164
So we're going back to a slaughter?

118
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:38,833
The Devil's work.

119
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:43,880
IDA: Okay, we're in. Bring us up.

120
00:07:44,464 --> 00:07:49,678
Ascension in three, two, one.

121
00:07:56,059 --> 00:07:58,728
BEAST: This is the darkness.

122
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:01,481
This is my domain.

123
00:08:01,564 --> 00:08:05,819
You little things that live in the light,

124
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:08,822
clinging to your feeble suns

125
00:08:08,905 --> 00:08:11,032
which die, in the end...

126
00:08:11,116 --> 00:08:14,119
ZACK: That's not the Ood.
Something is talking through them.

127
00:08:14,202 --> 00:08:17,330
BEAST: Only the darkness remains.

128
00:08:17,622 --> 00:08:21,418
This is Captain Zachary Cross Flane
of Sanctuary Base 6,

129
00:08:21,501 --> 00:08:23,795
representing the Torchwood Archive.

130
00:08:23,878 --> 00:08:26,297
You will identify yourself.

131
00:08:26,381 --> 00:08:28,591
You know my name.

132
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:30,218
What do you want?

133
00:08:30,301 --> 00:08:34,931
You will die here, all of you.
This planet is your grave.

134
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:37,809
It's him. It's him. It's him.

135
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:41,646
If you are the Beast, then answer me this.
Which one, hmm?

136
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:44,607
'Cause the universe has been busy
since you've been gone.

137
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:47,277
There's more religions
than there are planets in the sky.

138
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,612
The Arkiphets, Quoldonity,

139
00:08:49,738 --> 00:08:53,074
Christianity, Pash Pash, Neo-Judaism,

140
00:08:53,158 --> 00:08:56,494
San Claar, the Church of the Tin Vagabond.
Which devil are you?

141
00:08:56,578 --> 00:08:58,204
All of them.

142
00:08:58,288 --> 00:09:01,666
What, then you're the truth
behind the myth?

143
00:09:01,750 --> 00:09:05,795
This one knows me as I know him.

144
00:09:05,879 --> 00:09:09,299
The killer of his own kind.

145
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:12,177
How did you end up on this rock?

146
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:15,930
The Disciples of the Light
rose up against me

147
00:09:16,014 --> 00:09:20,143
and chained me in the Pit for all eternity.

148
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:21,603
When was this?

149
00:09:21,686 --> 00:09:23,188
Before time.

150
00:09:23,313 --> 00:09:24,647
What does that mean?

151
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:26,775
Before time.

152
00:09:26,858 --> 00:09:29,069
What did "before time" mean?

153
00:09:29,152 --> 00:09:33,948
Before time and light
and space and matter.

154
00:09:34,032 --> 00:09:36,576
Before the cataclysm.

155
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:40,413
Before this universe was created.

156
00:09:40,497 --> 00:09:43,833
That's impossible.
No life could have existed back then.

157
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:46,628
Is that your religion?

158
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:49,589
It's a belief.

159
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:54,344
You know nothing. All of you, so small.

160
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:58,473
The captain, so scared of command.

161
00:09:59,057 --> 00:10:03,853
The soldier,
haunted by the eyes of his wife.

162
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:08,483
The scientist, still running from daddy.

163
00:10:09,526 --> 00:10:12,487
The little boy who lied,

164
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:17,450
the virgin and the lost girl.

165
00:10:17,534 --> 00:10:20,745
So far away from home.

166
00:10:20,954 --> 00:10:23,039
The valiant child

167
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:26,876
who will die in battle so very soon.

168
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:30,630
-Doctor, what does that mean?
-Rose, don't listen.

169
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:32,132
What does it mean?

170
00:10:32,215 --> 00:10:34,217
You will die

171
00:10:35,260 --> 00:10:37,428
and I will live.

172
00:10:40,098 --> 00:10:41,599
What the hell was that?

173
00:10:41,683 --> 00:10:44,269
I had that thing inside my head.

174
00:10:45,645 --> 00:10:48,064
-Doctor, what did it mean?
-What do we do?

175
00:10:48,189 --> 00:10:50,859
Captain, what's the situation
with strategy nine?

176
00:10:50,942 --> 00:10:53,528
...the black hole, everything's true!

177
00:10:53,611 --> 00:10:54,988
We've lost pictures.

178
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:56,990
-How did it know...
-Did anyone get an analysis?

179
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:58,283
Jefferson.

180
00:10:58,366 --> 00:11:00,118
Stop. Everyone, just stop!

181
00:11:00,243 --> 00:11:02,245
-What do we do?
-Report...

182
00:11:02,328 --> 00:11:04,247
(RADIO FEEDBACK)

183
00:11:04,330 --> 00:11:06,124
If you want voices in the dark,
then listen to mine.

184
00:11:06,207 --> 00:11:08,710
That thing is playing on very basic fears.

185
00:11:08,793 --> 00:11:11,588
Darkness, childhood, nightmares,
all that stuff.

186
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:13,173
But that's how the Devil works.

187
00:11:13,256 --> 00:11:14,799
Or a good psychologist.

188
00:11:14,924 --> 00:11:17,427
How did it know about my father?

189
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:20,597
Okay, but what makes his version
of the truth any better than mine, hmm?

190
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:23,183
'Cause I'll tell you what I can see. Humans.

191
00:11:23,266 --> 00:11:27,228
Brilliant humans. Humans who travel
all the way across space.

192
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:30,940
Flying in a tiny little rocket
right into the orbit of a black hole,

193
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:33,943
just for the sake of discovery.
That's amazing!

194
00:11:34,027 --> 00:11:35,945
Do you hear me? Amazing. All of you.

195
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:40,867
The captain, his officer, his elder,
his juniors, his friends.

196
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:44,829
All with one advantage,
the Beast is alone, we are not.

197
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:47,290
If we can use that to fight against him...

198
00:11:52,420 --> 00:11:53,713
The cable's snapped!

199
00:11:53,796 --> 00:11:55,256
Get out!

200
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:07,101
Doctor, we lost the cable.
Doctor, are you all right?

201
00:12:07,185 --> 00:12:08,353
Doctor?

202
00:12:08,436 --> 00:12:10,939
-Comms are down.
-Doctor, can you hear me?

203
00:12:11,022 --> 00:12:13,608
I've still got life-signs,
but we've lost the capsule.

204
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:16,694
-ROSE: Say something! Are you there?
-There's no way out.

205
00:12:17,153 --> 00:12:18,529
They're stuck down there.

206
00:12:23,701 --> 00:12:25,662
DOCTOR: How much air have we got?

207
00:12:25,787 --> 00:12:27,497
Sixty minutes.

208
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:31,584
Fifty-five.

209
00:12:32,502 --> 00:12:33,878
But we've got to bring them back.

210
00:12:34,003 --> 00:12:37,548
They're ten miles down.
We haven't got another ten miles of cable.

211
00:12:37,632 --> 00:12:39,050
(THUDDING)

212
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:43,972
Captain, situation report?

213
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:03,241
It's the Ood. They're cutting through
the door bolts. They're breaking in.

214
00:13:03,366 --> 00:13:06,869
-Yes. Same on door 25.
-How long is it gonna take?

215
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:09,706
Well, it's only a basic frame.
Should take ten minutes.

216
00:13:12,375 --> 00:13:13,876
Eight.

217
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:18,715
I've got a security frame, might last
a bit longer but that doesn't help you.

218
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:22,468
Right. So we need to stop them
or get out or both.

219
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:25,346
I'll take both, yeah? But how?

220
00:13:25,430 --> 00:13:28,641
You heard the Doctor.
Why do you think that thing cut him off?

221
00:13:28,725 --> 00:13:30,101
'Cause he was making sense.

222
00:13:30,226 --> 00:13:32,729
He was telling you
to think your way out of this.

223
00:13:32,812 --> 00:13:35,064
Come on! For starters,
we need some lights.

224
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:37,191
Zack, there's got to be
some sort of power somewhere.

225
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:42,405
There's nothing I can do. Some captain!
Stuck in here, pressing buttons.

226
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:45,199
That's what the Doctor meant.
Press the right buttons.

227
00:13:45,283 --> 00:13:47,994
They've gutted the generators.

228
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:51,372
But the rocket's got an independent supply.

229
00:13:51,789 --> 00:13:53,750
If I could reroute that...

230
00:13:54,584 --> 00:13:57,670
Mr Jefferson, open the bypass conduits.

231
00:13:57,754 --> 00:13:59,714
Override the safety.

232
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:03,217
Opening bypass conduits, sir.

233
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:05,345
Channelling rocket feed.

234
00:14:06,929 --> 00:14:11,434
In three, two, one.

235
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:13,728
Power.

236
00:14:14,604 --> 00:14:15,897
There we go!

237
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:18,358
-Let there be light!
-What about that strategy nine thing?

238
00:14:18,441 --> 00:14:20,526
Not enough power, needs 100 percent.

239
00:14:20,610 --> 00:14:24,197
Right, we need a way out. Zack,
Mr Jefferson, you start working on that.

240
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,991
-Toby, what about you?
-I'm not a soldier. I can't do anything.

241
00:14:27,116 --> 00:14:29,994
No, you're the archaeologist.
What do you know about the Pit?

242
00:14:30,078 --> 00:14:31,954
Nothing, we can't even
translate the language.

243
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,415
-Right.
-Hold on. Maybe...

244
00:14:35,249 --> 00:14:36,501
What is it?

245
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:41,714
Since that thing was inside my head,
it's like the letters make more sense.

246
00:14:41,798 --> 00:14:46,010
Well, get to work.
Anything you can translate, just, anything.

247
00:14:46,803 --> 00:14:48,971
As for you, Danny boy,
you're in charge of the Ood.

248
00:14:49,097 --> 00:14:52,642
-Any way of stopping them?
-Well, I don't know.

249
00:14:52,934 --> 00:14:56,104
Then find out.
The sooner we get control of the base,

250
00:14:56,187 --> 00:14:59,524
the sooner we can get the Doctor out.
Now get going. Shift.

251
00:15:06,864 --> 00:15:10,576
We've got all this cable.
We might as well use it.

252
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:13,871
The drum is disconnected.
We could adapt it.

253
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:15,248
Feed it through.

254
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:17,333
DOCTOR: And then what?

255
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:20,711
Abseil into the Pit.

256
00:15:21,421 --> 00:15:23,005
Abseil. Right.

257
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:27,427
We're running out of air with no way back.
It's the only thing we can do,

258
00:15:27,510 --> 00:15:30,513
even if it's the last thing we ever achieve.

259
00:15:31,055 --> 00:15:34,475
I'll get back. Rose is up there.

260
00:15:34,559 --> 00:15:38,521
Well, maybe the key to that
is finding out what's in the Pit.

261
00:15:39,522 --> 00:15:42,608
Well, it's half of a good plan.

262
00:15:42,984 --> 00:15:44,444
What's the other half?

263
00:15:44,527 --> 00:15:47,071
I go down, not you.

264
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:53,035
Open junctions five, six, seven.

265
00:15:55,872 --> 00:15:59,417
Reroute filters 16 to 24. Go.

266
00:16:01,252 --> 00:16:04,130
There's all sorts of viruses
that could stop the Ood.

267
00:16:04,213 --> 00:16:07,133
Trouble is, we haven't got them on board.

268
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:09,343
Well, that's handy,
listing things we haven't got.

269
00:16:09,427 --> 00:16:13,055
We haven't got a swimming pool either,
or a Tesco's.

270
00:16:14,307 --> 00:16:17,852
Oh, my God. It says yes! I can do it!

271
00:16:18,436 --> 00:16:21,272
Hypothetically, if you flip the monitor,

272
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:25,151
broadcast a flare,
it can disrupt the telepathy. Brainstorm!

273
00:16:25,234 --> 00:16:28,613
-What happens to the Ood?
-It'll tank them, spark-out!

274
00:16:28,738 --> 00:16:31,073
There we are, then. Do it!

275
00:16:31,199 --> 00:16:32,742
I know, but...

276
00:16:33,618 --> 00:16:36,579
I'd have to transmit
from the central monitor.

277
00:16:36,704 --> 00:16:39,081
We need to go to Ood Habitation.

278
00:16:41,918 --> 00:16:43,628
That's what we'll do, then.

279
00:16:43,711 --> 00:16:47,048
-Mr Jefferson, sir, any way out?
-Just about.

280
00:16:47,173 --> 00:16:50,092
There's a network of maintenance tunnels
running underneath the base.

281
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:52,178
We should be able to
gain access from here.

282
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:53,679
Ventilation shafts.

283
00:16:53,763 --> 00:16:56,432
I appreciate the reference,
but there's no ventilation.

284
00:16:56,557 --> 00:16:58,434
No air, in fact, at all.

285
00:16:58,518 --> 00:17:02,021
They were designed for machines,
not life forms.

286
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:05,316
But I can manipulate
the oxygen field from here,

287
00:17:05,441 --> 00:17:08,027
create discrete pockets of atmosphere.

288
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:11,864
If I control it manually,
I can follow you through the network.

289
00:17:11,948 --> 00:17:16,702
Right. So we go down
and you make the air follow us by hand?

290
00:17:16,786 --> 00:17:18,538
You wanted me pressing buttons.

291
00:17:18,621 --> 00:17:22,583
Yep, I asked for it. Okay, we need to get
to Ood Habitation. Work out a route.

292
00:17:25,211 --> 00:17:28,464
IDA: That should hold it. How's it going?

293
00:17:28,589 --> 00:17:31,384
DOCTOR: Fine. Should work.

294
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:34,011
Doesn't feel like such a good idea now.

295
00:17:35,805 --> 00:17:39,350
Hmm. There it is again. That itch.

296
00:17:39,433 --> 00:17:41,602
Go down, go down, go down, go down!

297
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:43,479
The urge to jump.

298
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:46,524
Do you know where it comes from,
that sensation?

299
00:17:46,649 --> 00:17:51,737
Genetic heritage.
Ever since we were primates in the trees.

300
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:54,448
It's our body's way of testing us,

301
00:17:54,532 --> 00:17:58,661
calculating whether or not
we can reach the next branch.

302
00:17:58,995 --> 00:18:03,165
No, that's not it. That's too kind.

303
00:18:04,375 --> 00:18:07,336
It's not the urge to jump.
It's deeper than that.

304
00:18:07,878 --> 00:18:09,839
It's the urge to fall.

305
00:18:09,964 --> 00:18:11,465
Doctor!

306
00:18:13,384 --> 00:18:15,886
-You okay?
-Not bad, thanks.

307
00:18:16,971 --> 00:18:20,099
The wall of the Pit seems to be
the same as the cavern,

308
00:18:20,182 --> 00:18:22,852
just not much of it.

309
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:27,273
There's a crust about 20 feet down.

310
00:18:27,398 --> 00:18:28,941
And then...

311
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:31,694
nothing, just the Pit.

312
00:18:33,321 --> 00:18:35,698
Okay, then. Lower me down.

313
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:37,366
Well, here we go, then.

314
00:18:46,292 --> 00:18:49,462
-Danny!
-Hold on, just conforming.

315
00:18:49,545 --> 00:18:52,715
Danny, we've got to go now. Come on.

316
00:18:53,799 --> 00:18:54,967
There!

317
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:58,304
Put that in the monitor
and it's a bad time to be an Ood!

318
00:18:58,387 --> 00:19:00,222
We're coming back.
We're coming back to this room

319
00:19:00,348 --> 00:19:01,932
and we're getting the Doctor out.

320
00:19:02,058 --> 00:19:05,978
Danny, you go first, then Miss Tyler,
then Toby. I'll go last in defensive position.

321
00:19:06,062 --> 00:19:09,148
Now come on, quick as you can!

322
00:19:11,734 --> 00:19:14,445
God, it stinks. You all right?

323
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:17,239
Yeah, laughing. Which way do we go?

324
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:19,825
Just go straight ahead.
Keep going till I say so.

325
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,585
Not your best angle, Danny.

326
00:19:29,669 --> 00:19:31,170
Oi, stop it.

327
00:19:31,253 --> 00:19:33,089
-Don't know, could be worse.
-ROSE: Oi!

328
00:19:34,423 --> 00:19:38,344
Straight on till you find junction 7.1.
Keep breathing.

329
00:19:38,427 --> 00:19:41,305
I'm feeding you air. I've got you.

330
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,780
We're at 7.1, sir.

331
00:19:57,863 --> 00:19:59,740
Okay, I've got you.

332
00:20:02,785 --> 00:20:04,912
I'm just aerating the next section.

333
00:20:04,995 --> 00:20:08,374
Getting kind of cramped, sir.
Can't you hurry up?

334
00:20:08,457 --> 00:20:11,043
-I'm working on half power here.
-Stop complaining.

335
00:20:11,127 --> 00:20:13,421
-Mr Jefferson said stop complaining.
-I heard.

336
00:20:13,504 --> 00:20:15,798
-He heard.
-The air's getting a bit thin.

337
00:20:15,881 --> 00:20:18,384
-He's complaining now.
-I heard.

338
00:20:20,428 --> 00:20:23,431
-Danny, is that you?
-I'm not exactly happy.

339
00:20:23,514 --> 00:20:26,559
I'm just moving the air.
I've got to oxygenate the next section.

340
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:30,187
Now, keep calm or it's gonna feel worse.

341
00:20:30,271 --> 00:20:32,314
(METALLIC RATTLING)

342
00:20:34,316 --> 00:20:36,527
-What was that?
-Mr Jefferson, what was that?

343
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:39,530
-What was that noise?
-Captain, what was that?

344
00:20:39,822 --> 00:20:43,659
The junction in Habitation 5
has been opened. It must be the Ood.

345
00:20:44,118 --> 00:20:46,662
-They're in the tunnels.
-Open the gate.

346
00:20:46,787 --> 00:20:49,248
-I've got to get the air in!
-DANNY: Just open it, sir!

347
00:20:49,331 --> 00:20:52,877
-Where are they? Are they close?
-I can't tell. I can't see them.

348
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:55,880
The computer doesn't register Ood
as proper life forms.

349
00:20:56,005 --> 00:20:57,423
Whose idea was that?

350
00:20:57,506 --> 00:20:59,008
Open the gate!

351
00:21:03,179 --> 00:21:05,931
Danny, turn left, immediate left!

352
00:21:09,643 --> 00:21:13,105
The Ood, sir, can't you trap them?
Cut off the air?

353
00:21:13,189 --> 00:21:15,566
Not without cutting off yours.

354
00:21:19,862 --> 00:21:21,781
Danny, turn right, go right.

355
00:21:21,864 --> 00:21:24,200
Go faster. They're gonna catch up.

356
00:21:25,576 --> 00:21:27,953
I'll maintain defensive position.

357
00:21:28,037 --> 00:21:31,540
-You can't stop!
-Miss Tyler, that's my job.

358
00:21:31,624 --> 00:21:33,459
You've got your task, now see to it.

359
00:21:33,542 --> 00:21:35,878
You heard what he said, now shift!

360
00:21:53,270 --> 00:21:56,190
8.2, open 8.2!

361
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:58,692
Zack, open 8.2!

362
00:21:58,776 --> 00:22:01,320
-I've got to aerate it.
-Open it now!

363
00:22:01,403 --> 00:22:02,905
I'm trying!

364
00:22:04,740 --> 00:22:07,076
Danny, stop it. That's not helping!

365
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:08,994
Zack, get it open!

366
00:22:09,078 --> 00:22:12,665
Jefferson, I've got to open 8.2
by closing 8.1.

367
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:15,918
You've got to get past the junction,
now move!

368
00:22:16,836 --> 00:22:19,797
That's an order, now move!

369
00:22:23,676 --> 00:22:25,886
I'm gonna lose oxygen, Jefferson.

370
00:22:25,970 --> 00:22:28,180
I can't stop the automatics!

371
00:22:30,266 --> 00:22:33,102
That's it, come on, come on!

372
00:22:33,519 --> 00:22:36,856
Danny, turn left and head for 9.2.
That's the last one.

373
00:22:36,939 --> 00:22:40,109
Jefferson, you've got to move faster!

374
00:22:40,192 --> 00:22:41,402
John! Move! Move!

375
00:22:41,527 --> 00:22:44,321
-Mr Jefferson! Come on!
-Keep going!

376
00:22:48,242 --> 00:22:49,577
(PANTING)

377
00:22:50,578 --> 00:22:54,331
I regret to inform you, sir, I was a bit slow.

378
00:22:55,416 --> 00:22:57,042
Not so fast these days.

379
00:22:57,126 --> 00:23:02,047
I can't open 8.1, John.
Not without losing air for the others.

380
00:23:02,131 --> 00:23:04,008
And quite right, too, sir.

381
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:07,303
I think I bought them a little time.

382
00:23:08,512 --> 00:23:10,890
There's nothing I can do, John.

383
00:23:11,724 --> 00:23:14,685
-I'm sorry.
-You've done enough, sir.

384
00:23:14,810 --> 00:23:17,479
Made a very good captain
under the circumstances.

385
00:23:18,814 --> 00:23:23,444
Might I ask, if you can't add oxygen
to this section,

386
00:23:23,527 --> 00:23:26,405
can you speed up the process
of its removal?

387
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:29,241
I don't understand. What do you mean?

388
00:23:29,325 --> 00:23:32,745
Well, if I might choose the manner
of my departure, sir,

389
00:23:33,996 --> 00:23:37,333
lack of air seems more natural than, well...

390
00:23:39,001 --> 00:23:42,171
let's say, death by Ood.

391
00:23:42,713 --> 00:23:44,632
I'd appreciate it, sir.

392
00:23:45,549 --> 00:23:46,967
Godspeed, Mr Jefferson.

393
00:23:48,677 --> 00:23:50,012
Thank you, sir.

394
00:24:00,105 --> 00:24:05,152
Report.
Officer John Maynard Jefferson, PKD...

395
00:24:05,861 --> 00:24:08,948
deceased, with honours,

396
00:24:10,908 --> 00:24:13,118
43K 2.1.

397
00:24:13,202 --> 00:24:17,247
Zack, we're at the final junction.

398
00:24:18,457 --> 00:24:19,917
9.2.

399
00:24:21,377 --> 00:24:23,045
And, uh,

400
00:24:23,170 --> 00:24:27,216
if my respects could be on record,
he saved our lives.

401
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:31,387
Noted. Opening 9.2.

402
00:24:35,057 --> 00:24:38,727
ROSE: Lower 9.2! Zack, lower it!
DANNY: Back, back, back!

403
00:24:38,811 --> 00:24:42,731
We can't go back.
Look, 8.2's sealed off. We're stuck!

404
00:24:43,565 --> 00:24:45,359
Come on! Up!

405
00:24:52,825 --> 00:24:55,077
Come on. Toby, come on!

406
00:24:57,913 --> 00:24:59,707
Toby, get out of there!

407
00:24:59,790 --> 00:25:02,084
Help me. Oh, my God! Help me!

408
00:25:07,715 --> 00:25:09,216
It's this way!

409
00:25:22,730 --> 00:25:24,314
Hurry up!

410
00:25:27,276 --> 00:25:30,154
-Get it in.
-TOBY: Danny, get it done.

411
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:32,865
-Transmit!
-I'm trying. I'm trying. I'm getting it in...

412
00:25:32,948 --> 00:25:34,408
Stop them!

413
00:25:40,956 --> 00:25:43,542
ROSE: Danny, get that thing transmitting.

414
00:25:48,297 --> 00:25:50,132
(ELECTRONIC BUZZING)

415
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:08,984
You did it! We did it!

416
00:26:09,318 --> 00:26:11,320
Yes! Oh, yes!

417
00:26:13,947 --> 00:26:17,159
Zack, we did it. The Ood are down!
Now we've got to get the Doctor.

418
00:26:17,284 --> 00:26:18,786
I'm on my way.

419
00:26:20,662 --> 00:26:22,790
DOCTOR: You get representations
of the horned beast

420
00:26:22,873 --> 00:26:24,500
right across the universe,

421
00:26:24,625 --> 00:26:26,585
in the myths and legends
of a million worlds.

422
00:26:26,668 --> 00:26:30,297
Earth, Draconia, Vel Consadine.

423
00:26:31,006 --> 00:26:35,302
Daemos, the Kaled God of War.
It's the same image over and over again.

424
00:26:35,385 --> 00:26:39,640
Maybe that idea came from somewhere,

425
00:26:39,723 --> 00:26:41,517
bleeding through.

426
00:26:42,518 --> 00:26:44,853
A thought at the back
of every sentient mind.

427
00:26:44,978 --> 00:26:47,898
-Emanating from here?
-Could be.

428
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:50,859
But if this is the original,

429
00:26:50,943 --> 00:26:52,653
does that make it real?

430
00:26:53,570 --> 00:26:56,031
Does that make it the actual Devil, though?

431
00:26:56,115 --> 00:26:58,659
Well, if that's what you want to believe.

432
00:26:58,742 --> 00:27:02,287
Maybe that's what the Devil is
in the end, an idea.

433
00:27:05,874 --> 00:27:07,334
That's it.

434
00:27:08,585 --> 00:27:10,212
That's all we've got.

435
00:27:11,338 --> 00:27:13,132
You getting any sort of read out?

436
00:27:13,215 --> 00:27:14,591
Nothing.

437
00:27:15,467 --> 00:27:18,011
Could be miles to go yet.

438
00:27:18,095 --> 00:27:22,349
Or it could be 30 feet.
There's no way of telling.

439
00:27:25,185 --> 00:27:26,728
I could survive 30 feet.

440
00:27:26,812 --> 00:27:29,898
Oh, no, you don't. I'm pulling you back up.

441
00:27:32,985 --> 00:27:35,154
What are you doing?

442
00:27:35,237 --> 00:27:38,574
You bring me back, we're just
gonna sit there and run out of air.

443
00:27:39,950 --> 00:27:42,411
-I've got to go down.
-But you can't.

444
00:27:42,494 --> 00:27:44,079
Doctor, you can't!

445
00:27:44,163 --> 00:27:46,248
Call it an act of faith.

446
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:51,211
I don't want to die on my own.

447
00:27:52,588 --> 00:27:53,839
I know.

448
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:02,973
Doctor, are you there?
Doctor, Ida, can you hear me?

449
00:28:03,056 --> 00:28:04,474
The comms are still down.

450
00:28:04,558 --> 00:28:07,019
I can patch them through the central desk
and boost the signal.

451
00:28:07,102 --> 00:28:08,729
Just give me a minute.

452
00:28:13,275 --> 00:28:16,069
I didn't ask. Have you got any sort of faith?

453
00:28:16,945 --> 00:28:18,614
Not really.

454
00:28:19,865 --> 00:28:23,327
I was brought up
Neo-Classic Congregational.

455
00:28:24,077 --> 00:28:26,163
Because of my mum, she was...

456
00:28:29,458 --> 00:28:30,792
My old mum.

457
00:28:33,795 --> 00:28:35,756
But, no, I never believed.

458
00:28:35,964 --> 00:28:38,550
Neo-Classics. Have they got a devil?

459
00:28:38,967 --> 00:28:41,178
No, not as such. Just, um...

460
00:28:42,262 --> 00:28:44,473
the things that men do.

461
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:46,475
Same thing in the end.

462
00:28:46,558 --> 00:28:48,435
What about you?

463
00:28:54,316 --> 00:28:58,695
I believe... I believe
I haven't seen everything, I don't know.

464
00:29:02,908 --> 00:29:04,910
It's funny, isn't it?

465
00:29:04,993 --> 00:29:07,412
The things you make up, the rules.

466
00:29:07,496 --> 00:29:10,666
If that thing had said it came
from beyond the universe, I'd believe it.

467
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:13,085
But before the universe?

468
00:29:13,168 --> 00:29:14,753
Impossible.

469
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:18,423
Doesn't fit my rule.

470
00:29:21,343 --> 00:29:24,179
Still, that's why I keep travelling.

471
00:29:26,598 --> 00:29:28,558
To be proved wrong.

472
00:29:32,104 --> 00:29:33,397
Thank you, Ida.

473
00:29:34,690 --> 00:29:36,191
Don't go!

474
00:29:36,858 --> 00:29:39,486
If they get back in touch...

475
00:29:39,569 --> 00:29:42,614
If you talk to Rose, just tell her...

476
00:29:50,497 --> 00:29:51,957
Tell her...

477
00:29:55,627 --> 00:29:57,170
Oh, she knows.

478
00:30:01,008 --> 00:30:05,012
ROSE: Doctor, are you there?
Doctor, Ida, can you hear me?

479
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:07,514
Are you there, Doctor?

480
00:30:07,597 --> 00:30:08,807
He's gone.

481
00:30:10,559 --> 00:30:12,477
What do you mean, he's gone?

482
00:30:13,270 --> 00:30:14,730
He fell...

483
00:30:15,439 --> 00:30:17,232
into the Pit.

484
00:30:18,608 --> 00:30:22,321
And I don't know how deep it is,
miles and miles and miles.

485
00:30:22,404 --> 00:30:24,072
What do you mean, he fell?

486
00:30:24,239 --> 00:30:26,116
I couldn't stop him.

487
00:30:29,870 --> 00:30:31,413
He said your name.

488
00:30:37,794 --> 00:30:38,920
I'm sorry.

489
00:30:43,091 --> 00:30:44,092
Ida?

490
00:30:46,011 --> 00:30:50,474
There's no way of reaching you.
No cable, no backup.

491
00:30:50,557 --> 00:30:54,519
You're ten miles down. We can't get there.

492
00:30:54,770 --> 00:30:57,105
You should see this place, Zack.

493
00:31:02,277 --> 00:31:03,779
It's beautiful.

494
00:31:07,115 --> 00:31:10,077
I wanted to discover things,

495
00:31:12,496 --> 00:31:14,164
and here I am.

496
00:31:14,247 --> 00:31:16,583
We've got to abandon the base.

497
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:19,336
I'm declaring this mission unsafe.

498
00:31:19,419 --> 00:31:23,131
All we can do is make sure
no one ever comes here again.

499
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:25,884
But we'll never find out what it was.

500
00:31:25,967 --> 00:31:28,595
-Well, maybe that's best.
-Yeah.

501
00:31:33,475 --> 00:31:35,644
-Officer Scott...
-It's all right.

502
00:31:36,812 --> 00:31:38,230
Just go.

503
00:31:41,358 --> 00:31:42,943
Good luck.

504
00:31:43,026 --> 00:31:44,319
And you.

505
00:31:50,117 --> 00:31:54,663
Danny, Toby, close down the feed-links.
Get the retrotopes online.

506
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:58,041
Then get to the rocket
and strap yourselves in. We're leaving.

507
00:31:58,166 --> 00:31:59,918
I'm not going.

508
00:32:00,502 --> 00:32:02,045
Rose, there's space for you.

509
00:32:02,170 --> 00:32:06,383
No, I'm gonna wait for the Doctor,
just like he'd wait for me.

510
00:32:09,094 --> 00:32:11,680
I'm sorry, but he's dead.

511
00:32:13,014 --> 00:32:15,434
You don't know him.

512
00:32:15,517 --> 00:32:17,769
'Cause he's not.

513
00:32:18,937 --> 00:32:21,898
I'm telling you, he's not.

514
00:32:21,982 --> 00:32:25,235
And even if he was, how could I leave him

515
00:32:25,318 --> 00:32:27,529
all on his own, all the way down there?

516
00:32:27,612 --> 00:32:30,532
No, I'm... I'm gonna stay.

517
00:32:32,159 --> 00:32:34,119
Then I apologise for this.

518
00:32:34,202 --> 00:32:36,580
Danny, Toby, make her secure.

519
00:32:36,663 --> 00:32:40,750
No! No! No! Stop! No! Let me go!

520
00:32:40,834 --> 00:32:42,836
Get off me! I'm not leaving! No!

521
00:32:45,881 --> 00:32:49,968
I have lost too many people.
I am not leaving you behind.

522
00:32:52,596 --> 00:32:54,931
Let's get her on board.

523
00:32:58,602 --> 00:33:01,521
-Did that one just move?
-It's the telepathic field.

524
00:33:01,605 --> 00:33:05,317
-It's reasserting itself!
-Move it. Get to the rocket! Move!

525
00:33:13,992 --> 00:33:15,952
(GROANING SOFTLY)

526
00:33:20,665 --> 00:33:22,292
(GASPING)

527
00:33:26,379 --> 00:33:27,881
I'm breathing.

528
00:33:35,263 --> 00:33:37,682
Air cushion to support the fall.

529
00:33:39,267 --> 00:33:41,394
You can breathe down here, Ida.

530
00:33:41,478 --> 00:33:43,271
Can you hear me, Ida?

531
00:33:43,647 --> 00:33:46,858
Dislocating B clamp, C clamp.
Raising Blu-Nitro to maximum.

532
00:33:46,942 --> 00:33:50,195
-Toby, how's the Negapact feed-line?
-Clear, ready to go, sir.

533
00:33:50,278 --> 00:33:51,988
For God's sake, get us out of here!

534
00:33:52,113 --> 00:33:54,658
Captain, I think we're gonna have
a problem passenger.

535
00:33:54,783 --> 00:33:56,618
Keep an eye on her.

536
00:33:56,701 --> 00:33:59,287
-It's all right, Rose. We're safe.
-I'm not going anywhere!

537
00:33:59,412 --> 00:34:01,748
Get me out of this thing. Get me out!

538
00:34:01,831 --> 00:34:06,628
And liftoff!

539
00:34:07,504 --> 00:34:09,548
(WHOOPING)

540
00:34:20,308 --> 00:34:21,768
The rocket.

541
00:34:28,316 --> 00:34:30,527
Take me back to the planet.

542
00:34:31,528 --> 00:34:33,697
-Take me back!
-Or what?

543
00:34:34,489 --> 00:34:35,991
Or I'll shoot.

544
00:34:38,368 --> 00:34:41,496
Would you, though? Would you really?

545
00:34:41,705 --> 00:34:44,165
Is that what your Doctor would want?

546
00:34:51,214 --> 00:34:56,219
I'm sorry, but it's too late anyway.
Take a look outside. We can't turn back.

547
00:34:57,137 --> 00:35:00,682
This is what the Doctor would have wanted.
Isn't that right?

548
00:35:06,855 --> 00:35:10,025
History of some big battle.
Man against Beast.

549
00:35:10,150 --> 00:35:12,402
I don't know if you're getting this, Ida.
Hope so.

550
00:35:12,485 --> 00:35:16,489
Anyway, they defeated the Beast
and imprisoned it.

551
00:35:25,874 --> 00:35:28,209
And maybe that's the key.

552
00:35:35,925 --> 00:35:38,845
Or the gate or the bars.

553
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:41,056
(LOW GROWLING)

554
00:36:02,535 --> 00:36:03,912
What's the joke?

555
00:36:04,037 --> 00:36:07,457
Just... We made it. We escaped.

556
00:36:07,791 --> 00:36:09,668
-We actually did it.
-Not all of us.

557
00:36:09,751 --> 00:36:11,670
We're not out of it yet.

558
00:36:11,753 --> 00:36:15,256
We're still the first people in history
to fly away from a black hole.

559
00:36:15,382 --> 00:36:17,258
Toby, read me the stats.

560
00:36:17,342 --> 00:36:21,680
Gravity funnel holding, sir. Oh, it's holding.

561
00:36:21,763 --> 00:36:23,973
I accept that you exist.

562
00:36:25,308 --> 00:36:29,854
I don't have to accept what you are.
But your physical existence, I give you that.

563
00:36:30,105 --> 00:36:32,107
(BEAST GROWLING SOFTLY)

564
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:34,025
I don't understand.

565
00:36:34,109 --> 00:36:36,236
I was expected down here.

566
00:36:36,861 --> 00:36:39,114
I was given a safe landing and air.

567
00:36:40,073 --> 00:36:42,450
You need me for something. What for?

568
00:36:48,123 --> 00:36:50,041
Have I got to...

569
00:36:50,125 --> 00:36:54,212
I don't know, beg an audience or...
Is there a ritual?

570
00:36:54,295 --> 00:36:57,298
Some sort of incantation
or summons or spell?

571
00:36:57,382 --> 00:37:00,468
All these things I don't believe in,
are they real?

572
00:37:02,137 --> 00:37:04,472
Speak to me! Tell me!

573
00:37:08,309 --> 00:37:13,314
You won't talk or you can't talk.

574
00:37:16,443 --> 00:37:19,779
Hold on, hold on.
Wait a minute. Just let me...

575
00:37:20,697 --> 00:37:24,159
Oh! No. Yes! No.

576
00:37:24,784 --> 00:37:28,121
Think it through.
You spoke before, I heard your voice.

577
00:37:28,204 --> 00:37:32,000
An intelligent voice.
No, more than that. Brilliant!

578
00:37:34,252 --> 00:37:38,715
But looking at you now, all I can see...

579
00:37:42,510 --> 00:37:45,638
is beast.

580
00:37:46,431 --> 00:37:49,768
The animal, just the body.

581
00:37:49,851 --> 00:37:52,061
You're just the body, the physical form.

582
00:37:52,145 --> 00:37:54,898
What's happened to your mind, hmm?

583
00:37:56,065 --> 00:38:00,153
Where's it gone? Where's that intelligence?

584
00:38:03,198 --> 00:38:05,116
Oh, no.

585
00:38:07,494 --> 00:38:12,415
Stats at 53. Funnel stable at 66.5.
Hull pressure constant.

586
00:38:13,041 --> 00:38:15,877
Smooth as we can, sir.
All the way back home.

587
00:38:16,044 --> 00:38:18,797
Coordinates set for planet Earth.

588
00:38:20,215 --> 00:38:23,009
You were imprisoned a long time ago.

589
00:38:24,052 --> 00:38:28,181
Before the universe, after, sideways,
in between, it doesn't matter.

590
00:38:28,264 --> 00:38:30,683
The prison is perfect.

591
00:38:30,767 --> 00:38:35,230
It's absolute. It's eternal. Oh, yes!

592
00:38:35,730 --> 00:38:39,567
Open the prison, the gravity field collapses.

593
00:38:39,651 --> 00:38:42,403
This planet falls into the black hole.

594
00:38:43,655 --> 00:38:45,949
You escape, you die. Brilliant!

595
00:38:46,783 --> 00:38:51,496
But that's just the body.
The body is trapped, that's all.

596
00:38:53,122 --> 00:38:57,585
The Devil is an idea.
In all those civilisations, just an idea.

597
00:38:59,087 --> 00:39:02,632
But an idea is hard to kill.

598
00:39:02,799 --> 00:39:04,926
An idea can escape.

599
00:39:06,177 --> 00:39:11,349
The mind, the mind of the great Beast,
the mind can escape.

600
00:39:12,475 --> 00:39:16,563
Oh, but that's it!
You didn't give me air, your jailers did!

601
00:39:16,646 --> 00:39:20,567
They set this up all those years ago.

602
00:39:20,650 --> 00:39:22,986
They need me alive.

603
00:39:23,111 --> 00:39:26,781
Because if you're escaping,
then I've got to stop you!

604
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:35,248
If I destroy your prison,
your body is destroyed,

605
00:39:35,331 --> 00:39:37,667
your mind with it.

606
00:39:45,550 --> 00:39:49,804
But then you're clever enough
to use this whole system against me.

607
00:39:51,264 --> 00:39:54,767
If I destroy this planet,
I destroy the gravity field.

608
00:39:55,727 --> 00:39:57,186
The rocket.

609
00:39:57,979 --> 00:40:01,649
The rocket loses protection,
falls into the black hole.

610
00:40:04,277 --> 00:40:06,404
I have to sacrifice Rose.

611
00:40:08,781 --> 00:40:10,658
(LAUGHING)

612
00:40:14,120 --> 00:40:16,080
It doesn't make sense.

613
00:40:16,998 --> 00:40:19,959
We escaped, but there's a thousand ways
it could have killed us.

614
00:40:20,043 --> 00:40:23,046
It could have ripped out the air

615
00:40:23,129 --> 00:40:25,632
or, I don't know, burnt us or anything.

616
00:40:25,715 --> 00:40:28,176
But it let us go. Why?

617
00:40:29,802 --> 00:40:33,181
-Unless it wanted us to escape.
-Hey, Rose, do us a favour.

618
00:40:34,057 --> 00:40:35,516
Shut up.

619
00:40:37,226 --> 00:40:42,023
Almost there. We're beyond the reach
of the black hole in 40, 39...

620
00:40:42,148 --> 00:40:44,025
So that's the trap

621
00:40:44,150 --> 00:40:46,986
or the test or the final judgement,
I don't know.

622
00:40:48,988 --> 00:40:51,616
But if I kill you, I kill her.

623
00:40:56,871 --> 00:40:59,624
Except that implies

624
00:40:59,707 --> 00:41:03,461
in this big, grand scheme
of gods and devils,

625
00:41:03,544 --> 00:41:05,546
that she is just a victim.

626
00:41:05,672 --> 00:41:08,383
But I've seen a lot of this universe.

627
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:13,388
I've seen fake gods and bad gods
and demigods and would-be gods,

628
00:41:13,513 --> 00:41:17,725
and out of all that,
out of that whole pantheon,

629
00:41:17,809 --> 00:41:22,063
if I believe in one thing, just one thing,

630
00:41:23,731 --> 00:41:25,692
I believe in her.

631
00:41:30,738 --> 00:41:33,741
-What happened? What was that?
-What's he doing?

632
00:41:33,825 --> 00:41:37,328
-We've lost the funnel! Gravity collapse!
-What does that mean?

633
00:41:37,412 --> 00:41:40,665
We can't escape.
We're heading straight for the black hole.

634
00:41:51,092 --> 00:41:55,346
This is your freedom! Free to die!

635
00:41:55,430 --> 00:41:59,434
You're going into that black hole
and I'm riding with you!

636
00:42:04,897 --> 00:42:08,443
It's the planet. The planet's moving.

637
00:42:08,568 --> 00:42:10,361
It's falling.

638
00:42:11,821 --> 00:42:15,283
-I'm the rage and the bile and the ferocity!
-It's Toby!

639
00:42:15,408 --> 00:42:18,202
I am the prince and the fool and the agony!

640
00:42:18,286 --> 00:42:21,122
-I'm the sin and the fear and the darkness!
-It's him!

641
00:42:21,205 --> 00:42:25,835
Stay where you are. The ship's not stable.
What is he? What the hell is he?

642
00:42:29,464 --> 00:42:32,759
I shall never die!
The thought of me is forever.

643
00:42:32,842 --> 00:42:37,847
In the bleeding hearts of men,
in their vanity and obsession and lust!

644
00:42:37,972 --> 00:42:41,267
Nothing shall ever destroy me. Nothing.

645
00:42:41,350 --> 00:42:42,852
Go to hell.

646
00:42:54,489 --> 00:42:56,991
Emergency shield!

647
00:43:06,292 --> 00:43:10,088
We've still lost the gravity funnel.
We can't escape the black hole.

648
00:43:10,171 --> 00:43:13,091
But we stopped him.
That's what the Doctor would have done.

649
00:43:13,216 --> 00:43:15,259
Some victory.

650
00:43:15,510 --> 00:43:17,386
We're going in.

651
00:43:33,778 --> 00:43:37,698
The planet's lost orbit. It's falling!

652
00:44:04,851 --> 00:44:06,519
The planet's gone.

653
00:44:07,562 --> 00:44:09,730
-I'm sorry.
-Accelerate.

654
00:44:11,149 --> 00:44:12,733
I did my best.

655
00:44:13,734 --> 00:44:18,614
But, hey, the first human beings
to fall inside a black hole.

656
00:44:19,490 --> 00:44:21,075
How about that?

657
00:44:22,243 --> 00:44:23,744
History.

658
00:44:35,756 --> 00:44:37,425
What happened?

659
00:44:42,555 --> 00:44:44,432
We're turning.

660
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:49,770
We're turning around. We're turning away!

661
00:44:51,397 --> 00:44:53,566
DOCTOR: (ON RADIO)
Sorry about the hijack, Captain.

662
00:44:53,649 --> 00:44:56,027
This is the good ship Tardis.

663
00:44:56,110 --> 00:44:58,738
First things first,
have you got a Rose Tyler on board?

664
00:44:58,821 --> 00:45:03,409
I'm here! It's me! Oh, my God!
Where are you?

665
00:45:03,492 --> 00:45:06,370
I'm just towing you home.
Gravity-shmavity.

666
00:45:06,495 --> 00:45:09,832
My people practically invented black holes.
Well, in fact, they did.

667
00:45:09,916 --> 00:45:14,962
Couple of minutes, we'll be nice and safe.
Oh, and Captain, can we do a swap?

668
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:19,675
Say, if you give me Rose Tyler,
I'll give you Ida Scott. How about that?

669
00:45:19,759 --> 00:45:23,304
-She's alive!
-Yes. Thank you, God.

670
00:45:23,471 --> 00:45:26,515
Bit of oxygen starvation,
but she should be all right.

671
00:45:27,141 --> 00:45:29,352
I couldn't save the Ood.

672
00:45:29,435 --> 00:45:31,437
I only had time for one trip.

673
00:45:32,021 --> 00:45:34,190
They went down with the planet.

674
00:45:34,273 --> 00:45:35,816
(ELECTRONIC BEEPING)

675
00:45:36,692 --> 00:45:39,695
Entering clear space. End of the line.

676
00:45:39,820 --> 00:45:41,697
Mission closed.

677
00:46:01,842 --> 00:46:05,471
I don't know. I can't remember.

678
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:07,556
Well, it looked like a box.

679
00:46:07,640 --> 00:46:09,809
What do you mean, a box?

680
00:46:09,892 --> 00:46:13,896
Well, down in the hold, a big blue box.

681
00:46:14,021 --> 00:46:16,399
It just appeared. I don't know.

682
00:46:16,649 --> 00:46:20,903
DOCTOR: Zack we'll be off now.
Have a good trip home.

683
00:46:21,529 --> 00:46:25,032
And the next time
you get curious about something...

684
00:46:25,825 --> 00:46:29,078
Oh, what's the point?
You'll just go blundering in.

685
00:46:29,161 --> 00:46:30,246
The human race!

686
00:46:30,371 --> 00:46:33,499
But, Doctor, what did you find down there?

687
00:46:33,624 --> 00:46:35,376
That creature, what was it?

688
00:46:35,459 --> 00:46:39,088
I don't know.
Never did decipher that writing.

689
00:46:39,213 --> 00:46:40,464
But that's good.

690
00:46:40,548 --> 00:46:43,217
The day I know everything,
I might as well stop.

691
00:46:43,342 --> 00:46:46,095
What do you think it was, really?

692
00:46:46,178 --> 00:46:50,224
I think we beat it.
That's good enough for me.

693
00:46:50,308 --> 00:46:52,893
It said I was going to die in battle.

694
00:46:55,104 --> 00:46:56,605
Then it lied.

695
00:46:58,232 --> 00:47:02,111
Right! Onwards, upwards.
Ida, see you again maybe.

696
00:47:02,194 --> 00:47:03,404
I hope so.

697
00:47:03,529 --> 00:47:05,573
And thanks, boys!

698
00:47:05,656 --> 00:47:09,076
Hang on though, Doctor,
you never really said.

699
00:47:09,243 --> 00:47:12,538
You two, who are you?

700
00:47:12,621 --> 00:47:16,167
Oh, the stuff of legend.

701
00:47:17,877 --> 00:47:19,754
(WHOOSHING)

702
00:47:19,837 --> 00:47:24,592
This is the final report of Sanctuary Base 6.

703
00:47:24,800 --> 00:47:29,513
Officer Tobias Zed, deceased, with honours.

704
00:47:30,181 --> 00:47:33,100
43K 2.1.

705
00:47:33,434 --> 00:47:37,355
Also, Ood 1 Alpha 1,

706
00:47:37,438 --> 00:47:40,483
deceased, with honours.

707
00:47:40,566 --> 00:47:44,278
Ood 1 Alpha 2, deceased, with honours...

708
00:47:52,286 --> 00:47:54,121
Lights!

709
00:47:55,498 --> 00:47:57,458
I am your salvation.

710
00:47:57,541 --> 00:47:58,709
(WHOOSHING)

711
00:47:58,793 --> 00:48:00,836
The sound of the universe.

712
00:48:00,920 --> 00:48:02,588
What does it mean?

713
00:48:03,714 --> 00:48:06,133
-His name is the Doctor.
-Doctor what?

714
00:48:06,217 --> 00:48:08,135
Find me that girl!

715
00:48:09,678 --> 00:48:12,973
Here we are, complete strangers,
and I'm flashing you my knickers.

716
00:48:13,057 --> 00:48:15,810
One step closer to catching the Doctor.

717
00:48:15,976 --> 00:48:17,395
Don't I know you?

